16/09/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- US Brigadier General Louis W. Weber, commander of NATO Sarajevo HQ, paid his first official visit to the BiH Joint Staff on Thursday (15 September).
He discussed the process of upcoming defence reforms and the strengthening of co-operation between NATO HQ and BiH's defence institutions.
BiH Chief of Joint Staff General Sifet Podzic said he hopes the defence law will be adopted next month, so that reforms can be implemented.
(PBS BiH, Fena, RTRS - 15/09/05)
